description: From late Middle English herbergen (“to lodge”), a back-formation from herberjour. Compare harbinger, harbour.

verbs.description: harbinge (third-person singular simple present harbinges, present participle harbinging, simple past and past participle harbinged)
harbinge (third-person singular simple present harbinges, present participle harbinging, simple past and past participle harbinged)

entries.meaning: (rare, neologism) To be a harbinger; to presage.
